    tips: "Veal is at its best with a trace of pink — fully cooked veal is dry and flavourless. The chops should reach 62°C at the thickest part. The flaming of the Calvados is not dramatic performance — it burns off the harsh alcohol, leaving the apple and oak aromas.",
