    accent: "#c8a840", servings: 4,
    description: "A Provençal variation on the American classic: poached eggs placed on brandade de morue (salt cod emulsion) on a croûte, then napped with hollandaise. The saltiness of the cod, the richness of the yolk, and the buttery hollandaise create one of the most satisfying brunch dishes in the canon.",
