    accent: "#5a3010", servings: 8,
    description: "One of the great classical sauces of Carême's era, originally made with real turtle — now invariably made with calf's head. A rich, complex blend of demi-glace, Madeira, tomatoes, and an infusion of aromatic herbs including basil, marjoram, and sage. Served with tête de veau and braised offal.",
