    description: "The Lyon bouchon salad: frisée (curly endive) dressed with hot lardons whose fat creates the dressing, finished with a splash of vinegar that sizzles in the pan, and topped with a poached egg. One of the great composed salads — the runny yolk mixing with the warm bacon vinaigrette is entirely good.",
